The app is not flexible on the value of pi, meaning it doesn't allow you to put your desired value for pi. What this means is that if anyone uses this app to solve a given problem, you're likely to be wrong if you're given a different value for pi to work through to your answer. Pi as we know is a long number and you could be given pi=3.14, 3.1415, 3.14159, 22/7, 3.1428 and so on. So if this app doesn't allow you to change the value of pi, then you're likely to be wrong with your final answer
